ome.smuggler.core.service.file

Interface KeyValueStore<K extends util.object.Identifiable,V>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    KeyValueFileStore, MemoryKeyValueStore, TSafeKeyValueStore

    public interface KeyValueStore<K extends util.object.Identifiable,V>
    A persistent key-value store that associates a value V to an Identifiable key.

    • Method Detail

      • put

        void put(K key,
         V value)
        Maps a key to a value. If the specified key is already associated to a value, the old value will be overwritten.
        Parameters:
        key - identifies the mapping.
        value - the value to store.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any argument is null.

        The following checked exceptions are rethrown as unchecked (i.e. the exception is masked as a runtime exception and thrown as is without wrapping it in a RuntimeException):
        IOException if an I/O occurs.

      • get

        default V get(K key)
        Gets the value associated to the specified key.
        Parameters:
        key - identifies the mapping.
        Returns:
        the value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the argument is null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if no value is associated to the given key.

        The following checked exceptions are rethrown as unchecked (i.e. the exception is masked as a runtime exception and thrown as is without wrapping it in a RuntimeException):
        IOException if an I/O occurs.

      • modify

        void modify(K key,
            java.util.function.Function<V,V> operation)
        Updates the value associated to the specified key.
        Parameters:
        key - identifies the mapping.
        operation - is given the current value, does something with it and then returns the new value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any argument is null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if no value is associated to the given key.

        The following checked exceptions are rethrown as unchecked (i.e. the exception is masked as a runtime exception and thrown as is without wrapping it in a RuntimeException):
        IOException if an I/O occurs.

      • remove

        void remove(K key)
        Deletes the mapping identified by the specified key. Does nothing if no value is currently associated to the key.
        Parameters:
        key - identifies the mapping.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the argument is null.

        The following checked exceptions are rethrown as unchecked (i.e. the exception is masked as a runtime exception and thrown as is without wrapping it in a RuntimeException):
        IOException if an I/O occurs.
